Introduction
\layout Standard

Ghf is an IDE (Integrated Development Environment) for the programming language
 Haskell.
 It is written in Haskell.
 Ghf is intended as a practical tool to support the Haskell development
 process.
 The development has been started because no such tools were available at
 this time.
 The development of an IDE is a big issue, so Ghf is intended to become
 a community project and everyone is invited to contribute.
 If you are a user or just test Ghf, we would appreciate to here from you
 and problems and wishes for Ghf.
\layout Standard

Ghf uses GTK+ as GUI Toolkit with the gtk2hs binding.
 It is plattform independend and should run on any plattform where GTK+,
 gtk2hs and ghc can be installed.
 (It is currently been tested on Windows and Linux).
 It uses the Cabal package management and build system for Package Management.
 It uses Haddock for source code documentation.
 It currently only supports the Glasgow Haskell Compiler (ghc).
 It would be possible to integrated with other compilers, but their are
 no plans to do this.
