Version numbering
\layout Standard

We have adopted the following policy for numbering Ghf versions: Stable
 Releases are numbered x.y, where y is even.
 Releases on the stable branch x.y are numbered x.y.z, where z (>= 1) is the
 patchlevel number.
 Patchlevels are bug-fix releases only, and never change the user interface
 in a substantial way.
\layout Standard

Development releases are numbered x.y.z, where y is uneven.
 
\layout Standard

The version number of your copy of Ghf can be found by invoking ghf with
 the --version flag or by looking in the Help/About box.
